{
  "texts": [
    "Once the data were expressed according to a near-normal distribution, we trained the model for 200 epochs, including an early stopping criterion.",
    "The estimated parameters were set to initialize the subsequent steps.",
    "Specifically, with the initialization parameters available, we removed the logarithmic transformation and trained the model directly in the original landslide area density scale.",
    "This step was further run over 200 epochs, and the resulting parameters were fine-tuned to match the overall landslide area density distribution.",
    "In other words, we re-introduced the 1 km grids with zero density at this stage."
  ]
}